{
  "texts": [
    "Currently, ensemble methods dominate AL, but integrating Bayesian models, renowned for their efficacy (88), could significantly enhance the exploration of chemical spaces.",
    "Transitioning to the next phase of development, hybrid systems that merge exploratory and trained methodologies present a promising path for comprehensive chemical space exploration.",
    "Rule-based systems efficiently probe molecular structures akin to identified hits.",
    "In contrast, trained generative algorithms have proven effective in refining structures within explored chemical spaces.",
    "A cohesive de novo drug generation pipeline might first employ AL for rapid hit discovery, followed by Rule-Based systems for initial optimization."
  ]
}